@meco 1
@start npc-line

// Mundane conversations overheard from civilians on a busy space station.

# npc-line
- [5] @arrival-line
- [5] @canteen-line
- [4] @work-line
- [4] @station-life-line
- [3] @travel-line
- [3] @rumour-line
- [2] @neighbour-line

# arrival-line
- I travelled @journey-distance to reach @station-name! @friendly-question
- It took me @travel-time to get to @station-name. @arrival-reaction
- My shuttle finally docked at @station-name. @friendly-question
- You would not believe how many connections it takes to reach @station-name.
- This is my first time on @station-name. I expected it to be @station-expectation.

# journey-distance
- a long way
- three systems
- all the way from @origin
- farther than I care to admit
- halfway across the sector

# travel-time
- two days
- eleven hours
- most of the week
- longer than the ticket promised
- three transfers and a very uncomfortable night

# arrival-reaction
- I could sleep for a week.
- At least my luggage made it this time.
- I am never booking the cheap route again.
- Now I just need to remember where I rented a room.
- The artificial gravity still feels a little strange.

# station-expectation
- quieter
- cleaner
- smaller
- easier to navigate
- less crowded

# friendly-question
- How's your day, friend?
- Has the station been treating you well?
- Know anywhere quiet to sit?
- Is the coffee always this bad?
- You waiting for a shuttle too?

# canteen-line
- I saw the @canteen-worker pour @strange-liquid into @soup. I'm not looking forward to trying it.
- The @dish smells @food-smell today. I think I'll stick to ration bars.
- They changed the menu at @canteen-name again. Somehow it got worse.
- If you're heading to @canteen-name, avoid the @dish. Trust me.
- I asked what was in the @dish. The @canteen-worker just changed the subject.
- The coffee at @canteen-name is strong enough to clean engine parts.

