# rumour-line
- I heard that @rumour-event. Probably just station gossip.
- A dockworker told me that @rumour-event. I don't believe it, but I did lock my door.
- Did you hear? Apparently @rumour-event. This station never stays boring for long.
- Maintenance found @strange-find in @maintenance-place. They won't say how it got there.
- Someone on @deck-name keeps ordering @odd-cargo. I try not to ask questions.

# rumour-event
- a maintenance drone opened a door that wasn't on the map
- someone has been sleeping in an empty cargo pod
- the station clock lost seven minutes last night
- a courier arrived with a crate that was humming
- an entire shuttle crew checked in under the same name
- the observation windows showed the wrong stars for almost a minute

# strange-find
- a boot with no owner
- three hundred identical spoons
- a warm spacesuit
- an old navigation computer
- a crate addressed to the station itself

# maintenance-place
- an air duct
- a sealed service tunnel
- the back of lift four
- a disused cargo locker
- the ventilation intake

# deck-name
- habitation deck four
- the agricultural ring
- customs level
- the old command deck
- the visitor concourse

# odd-cargo
- empty glass jars
- antique door handles
- live soil
- left-handed gloves
- crates marked “definitely not fragile”

# neighbour-line
- My neighbour practices the same song every artificial morning. They only know the loud part.
- The family in the next cabin adopted a cleaning drone. It follows me home now.
- Someone upstairs keeps moving furniture during the night cycle. We don't have an upstairs.
- The cabin beside mine has been empty for months, but its alarm goes off every morning.
- I lent my neighbour a spanner three weeks ago. At this point, I think it belongs to them.

# station-name
- Kepler Junction
- Orison Gate
- Helix Nine
- Meridian Station
- Port Caligo
- Lagrange Rest
- Cinder Dock
- Vesper Relay

// Experimental fully compositional POC entry point. It is intentionally not
// the default: its broad role cross-products create more combinations, but the
// curated domain-specific frames above produce more believable dialogue.

